Body elongate oval, moderately convex, dorsum covered with white pubescence (Fig. 5
a-c
). Head yellow. Antennae and mouthparts yellowish brown. Pronotum yellow. Scutellum black. Elytra black with apical margin narrowly brown. Prothoracic hypomeron yellow. Prosternum brown. Mesoventrite, metaventrite and elytral epipleura black. Legs yellowish brown.

Male genitalia. Penis stout (Fig. 5e); penis capsule highly sclerotized with tiny inner arm and large outer arm; apex of penis with membranous appendage (Fig. 5f). Tegmen stout (Fig. 5
g-h
) with penis guide slightly constricted at base, widest at basal 1/4 length, then tapering gradually to pointed apex in ventral view (Fig. 5g) and its apex curved outwardly in lateral view (Fig. 5h). Parameres elongate oval, shorter than penis guide, sparsely setose at apices (Fig. 5h).
